# Army builder (`projects/army-builder/`)

Valour & Fortitude napoleonic army list builder. Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS.

## Architecture

- Single `state` object in `app.js` holds catalog, sheet, entries, brigades, UI state
- DOM helpers: `$()`, `showError()`, screen toggles between setup and builder
- PDF export uses vendored `jspdf.umd.min.js` — avoid editing it
- `fate-cards.js` is a separate module for fate card logic
- Game reference data in `data/`; user army lists in localStorage (not the repo)

## Style

- Plain functions, no classes or modules (except fate-cards)
- Use existing patterns: `fmtWeapon()`, `fmtStats()`, `figureBounds()`, etc.
- CSS in `style.css` — keep class names consistent with `index.html`

## API paths

App fetches `/api/catalog` and `/api/army/:id` — mapped to `data/` via `netlify.toml`.

